Come hang out with <b>Alex</b>, our featured citizen of the week!<br><br>Alex has been holding down the fort at <a href='/home/?user=alexpg'>40167 Pyramid Drive</a> in Ravenwood ever since August 15th, 2006. <br><br>Alex describes himself as very outgoing, so it should be no surprise that he's also a really friendly guy. <br><br>His interests include skydiving, animals, and football. So he should have no problem catching a pass at 13,000 feet while doing a little bird watching.<br><br>Speaking of animals, one of Alex's favorite colors is Zebra. You may have not known that Zebra is a color, but if you check your color chart you'll find that it's right in between Cow and Tiger.<br><br>When he's not hanging out in the Tree House, the Pizza Place, or the Arcade, Alex is probably jamming out to his favorite Classic Rock and heavy metal. Alex also likes to throw in some Big Band to mix up the selection. <br><br>Throw on a movie in Alex's screening room and kick back. Or you can enjoy some tunes on his turntables. <br><br>If the written word is more your thing, you'll want to check out Alex's Svendi bookcase. There's a built in chair so you won't have to stray too far from the bookshelf before you dive into that scintillating read. <br><br>Next time you see Alex, give him a pat on the back and thank him for being such a great citizen.<br></div>
